Best-selling author Wade Rouse’s pseudonym, Viola Shipman, is the name of his late maternal grandmother, a woman who had a profound influence on his life.
Viola Shipman and Wade Rouse (Photo: Wade Rouse)“Their sacrifices really changed the course of my family’s life and my life.
Best-selling author Wade Rouse (Photo: Wade Rouse)“For (Viola), gardening was the one thing we could do that provided solace for her, my mom and I.
In “The Heirloom Garden,” Iris Maynard is a woman who’s no stranger to loss, having outlived her husband and daughter.
There, Iris’ flowers have become her new family, her heirloom garden filled with memories of her loved ones.